:[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic-access class mapping**\\n\\nI'm thinking about dynamic-access class mapping, but it seems like there’s an issue with only using the test class. I wonder if I need a custom subclass. From my understanding, StAXResult isn't final, which is worth checking. I should look into the constructors too, as it appears that javax.transform.stax.StAXResult has public constructors like XMLStreamWriter and XMLEventWriter. I need to gather more details to figure this out!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting NoClassDefFoundError**\\n\\nI’m examining the issue of missing a class which could cause a NoClassDefFoundError. It seems like the constant pool resolution of fields could be involved here. I wonder if the method references get resolved when executing getSourceImpl or createResult. Class verification might also play a role. I should check the build dependencies and my Java version—currently, I have JDK 21 but need to consider HSQLDB 2.4.1 possibly requiring the jaxb API. Adding testRuntime seems necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hX5twbnX1P2WsJxKVGDuV9jt|fc_0cc8f5a4eda32df9016a115bde96a88193b2b5268d91afefe6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"jaxb-api|javax.xml.bind\" tests/src/org.hsqldb tests/src -g build.gradle -g '*.java' | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3552, "output": 910, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21870, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779522511440, "responseId": "resp_0cc8f5a4eda32df9016a115bcfe50c81939e5cda152cd84005"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_hX5twbnX1P2WsJxKVGDuV9jt|fc_0cc8f5a4eda32df9016a115bde96a88193b2b5268d91afefe6", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/tools.jackson.jaxrs/jackson-jaxrs-json-provider/3.1.2/bui