 curious about how the dynamic-access report defines \\\"covered.\\\" It might stem from the agent's instrumentation of JVM APIs. I'll need to examine the build output after the external run to see if the tests executed properly, especially since the XML indicates two tests were run.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KtuUnxlxY8QfiiuTwbQ1IJSf|fc_0cc8f5a4eda32df9016a115daa71a88193a46a3c30a31ceb2c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/build -type f | grep -E 'dynamic|access|coverage|trace|metadata|calls|agent|reflection' | sort | sed -n '1,200p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 25079, "output": 589, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 64580, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779522972643, "responseId": "resp_0cc8f5a4eda32df9016a115d9ea7ec81939f5519143f9b0d73"}}
